Five people are facing charges of murder, defeating the ends of justice, kidnapping and attempted murder in connection with the killing of Zenzele and Mgcini Coka. eNCA/Siphamandla Goge JOHANNESBURG - The five men accused of killing the Coka brothers have been granted bail. The accused have been granted R10,000 bail each. READ: Coka brothers killing | Lead investigator says case could destabilise country The men are facing charges of murder, defeating the ends of justice, kidnapping, and attempted murder. Zenzele and Mgcini Coka were killed during an altercation on a farm in Mkhondo.